ZH: 我们等了很久，终于看到了绿灯。
EN: We waited for a long time and finally saw the green light.

ZH: 请等到绿灯亮起后再过马路。
EN: Please wait until the green light is on before crossing the road.

ZH: 每天早上，我都会在红绿灯等候。
EN: Every morning, I wait at the traffic lights at the intersection.

ZH: 超市门口的绿灯被撞坏了，需要维修。
EN: The green light at the supermarket entrance is broken and needs repair.

ZH: 在绿灯亮起时，车辆可以通行。
EN: Vehicles are allowed to pass when the green light is on.

ZH: 过马路时，看到绿灯要记得走。
EN: When crossing the road, remember to walk when you see the green light.

ZH: 停车等候绿灯时，手机可用来打发时间。
EN: You can use your phone to pass the time while waiting for the green light.

ZH: 当绿灯变成黄灯时，要准备停车。
EN: Prepare to stop when the green light turns yellow.

ZH: 他们在十字路口等待着绿灯的亮起。
EN: They are waiting for the green light to come on at the intersection.

ZH: 在高速公路上，我总是保持绿灯速度。
EN: I always maintain the green light speed on the highway.

ZH: 在车流量大的时候，绿灯时间会拉长。
EN: The green light time will be extended when there is heavy traffic.

ZH: 当绿灯出现时，大家都可以安全过马路。
EN: Everyone can safely cross the road when the green light appears.

ZH: 在路口等待绿灯的时间总是很漫长。
EN: The waiting time for the green light at the intersection is always very long.

ZH: 绿灯对于车辆通行至关重要。
EN: The green light is crucial for the passage of vehicles.

ZH: 当看到绿灯亮起时，他们终于松了口气。
EN: They finally breathed a sigh of relief when they saw the green light come on.

ZH: 等待绿灯的时间似乎永无止境。
EN: The wait for the green light seems endless.

ZH: 绿灯不断地闪烁，表示可以通行。
EN: The green light keeps flashing, indicating that it is safe to pass.

ZH: 在绿灯前停下来，是一个负责的交通行为。
EN: Stopping before the green light is a responsible traffic behavior.

ZH: 我们所有人都很迫切地等待着绿灯的亮起。
EN: We are all eagerly awaiting the green light to come on.

ZH: 交通管理部门定期检查绿灯的使用情况。
EN: The traffic management department regularly inspects the use of green lights.
